# Lightning Strike Trigger

triggers.YetAnotherHelper/LightningStrikeTrigger.placements.name.normal=Lightning Strike Trigger

triggers.YetAnotherHelper/LightningStrikeTrigger.attributes.description.playerOffset=The X offset of the lightning relative to the player's position.
triggers.YetAnotherHelper/LightningStrikeTrigger.attributes.description.verticalOffset=The Y offset of the lightning relative to the player's position.
triggers.YetAnotherHelper/LightningStrikeTrigger.attributes.description.strikeHeight=The height of the lightning strike. If set to 0, the height will be the screen's height.
triggers.YetAnotherHelper/LightningStrikeTrigger.attributes.description.seed=The seed for the randomizer which generates the lightning strike.
triggers.YetAnotherHelper/LightningStrikeTrigger.attributes.description.delay=The delay, in seconds, between the player entering the trigger and the appearance of the lightning strike.
triggers.YetAnotherHelper/LightningStrikeTrigger.attributes.description.rain=Upon lightning strike, rain will begin falling in the level.
triggers.YetAnotherHelper/LightningStrikeTrigger.attributes.description.flash=Upon lightning strike, the screen will flash white.
triggers.YetAnotherHelper/LightningStrikeTrigger.attributes.description.constant=If lightning should constantly strike while the player is inside the trigger.

# Remove Light Sources Trigger

triggers.YetAnotherHelper/RemoveLightSourcesTrigger.placements.name.normal=Remove Light Sources Trigger

triggers.YetAnotherHelper/RemoveLightSourcesTrigger.attributes.description.offsetTo=Determines how the lighting changes passing through the trigger.
triggers.YetAnotherHelper/RemoveLightSourcesTrigger.attributes.description.offsetFrom=Determines how the lighting changes passing through the trigger backwards.
triggers.YetAnotherHelper/RemoveLightSourcesTrigger.attributes.description.onlyOnce=If checked, the trigger will be disabled when the player first leaves it.
triggers.YetAnotherHelper/RemoveLightSourcesTrigger.attributes.description.positionMode=Determines which direction the lighting fades towards.

# Spawn Jelly Trigger

triggers.YetAnotherHelper/SpawnJellyTrigger.placements.name.normal=Spawn Jelly Trigger

triggers.YetAnotherHelper/SpawnJellyTrigger.attributes.description.onlyOnce=If set to false, jellies will spawn every time the player enters the trigger again.
